New Records: Damian Lillard scored 26 points and Giannis Antetokounmpo had 25 points, 16 rebounds, and 8 assists in the Bucks' win over the Spurs.
Damian Lillard had 8 assists and Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded 3 assists in the first quarter.
Brook Lopez scored 22 points, including 17 in the first half, and AJ Green and Gary Trent each added 14 points.
Keldon Johnson led the Spurs with 24 points, Chris Paul added 18 points, and Devin Vassell contributed 11 points.
Victor Wembanyama had 10 points, 10 rebounds, and 3 blocks for the Spurs.
Key Match Events: Antetokounmpo blocked Vassell's dunk attempt and Lopez made a 3-pointer to extend the lead by 19 at halftime.
The Bucks went on a 32-13 run after the game was tied early in the second quarter.
Milwaukee's 3-point shooting was strong, making 12 out of 24 attempts in the first half.
Pre-Game Insights: Jeremy Sochan, averaging 13.4 points per game, sat out for the Spurs due to a back injury.
The Spurs had no players in double figures in the first half and struggled with 3-point shooting, making 18 out of 52 attempts.
Post-Match Reflections: The Bucks led by 26 points in the fourth quarter and dominated the game after their strong first half performance.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was notable for the Bucks' overall dominance, particularly in the first half, and the key moments that shifted momentum in their favor.
